{"TopicId":119999,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Trackingstation Ambientlight [v0.3.4, 2021-08-25]","CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-02T20:33:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-02T20:33:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrackingstation Ambientlight is a small mod that allows you to brighten the dark side of planets in the trackingstation by editing the ambientlight color via a config file.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/895/Trackingstation%20Ambientlight\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESpacedock\u003C/a\u003E or via \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/197082-c\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSource: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/mhoram-kerbin/TrackingStationAmbientlight\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLicense: GNU GPL-3.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCompatibility:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisables itself when \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/64901-1\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EAmbient Light Adjustment\u003C/a\u003E is installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScreenshot of the difference this mod makes:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222glWk7Z.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/2glWk7Z.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven crazy stuff is possible since all RGB components are editable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022YugWPrV.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/YugWPrV.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/mhoram-kerbin/TrackingStationAmbientlight/blob/master/changelog.txt\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EChangelog\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimilar mods:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/189071-1\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPlanetshine\u003C/a\u003E: adjust ambient lightning in flight mode and much more\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/64901-1\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EAmbient Light Adjustment\u003C/a\u003E: adjust ambient lightning globally\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/190080-1\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EMinimum Ambient Lighting\u003C/a\u003E: adjust ambient lightning in flight mode and in the space center\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-25T18:19:15Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2021 06:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by mhoram\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EUpdate to KSP 1.12.2\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZobrAA","CreatedById":65233,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-04T02:58:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhy only in Tracking Station? In the Map View this will be truly useful \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":".50calBMG","CreatedById":150444,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-04T04:22:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI believe you can already do it in map view if you use Planet Shine\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mrclucks","CreatedById":139561,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-04T07:19:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ethere\u0027s also an ambient lighting mod which is similar to what you\u0027re doing but just brightens the dark side of everything(including your craft) to whatever level you select on the slider\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Senshi","CreatedById":57692,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-04T07:22:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENice idea, but\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/71536-1-0-4-Ambient-Light-Adjustment-1-4-4-2-30-06-15-(continued)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/71536-1-0-4-Ambient-Light-Adjustment-1-4-4-2-30-06-15-(continued)\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eoffers the same, with a nice minimal GUI. Except the color change, but I can\u0027t see a use for that.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-04T08:43:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBefore writing this addon, I found three mods that change the ambientlightning:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPlanetshine can adjust the ambient light in flight mode (flight mode includes map mode).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAccording to the Description of Ambient Light Adjustment it changes the ambient lightning only in the flight mode.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/67641\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMinimum Ambient Lighting\u003C/a\u003E can change the ambient lightning in flight mode and the space center.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESince none of them handle the tracking station, I thought it to be beneficial to extend this functionality to the Tracking Station.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI just had a look into the source of \u0022Ambient Light Adjustment\u0022 an it uses \u0022KSPAddon.Startup.EveryScene\u0022, so it sets the ambient light also in the tracking station, which is a discrepancy from its description. So thanks for bringing this to my attention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENonetheless i think of the tracking station as a sandbox, where one should get all information about the planet, while in flight mode it should be tough to land on the dark side of a planet. And none of the other mods provide this.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-09-04T09:06:55Z\u0022 title=\u002209/04/2015 09:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 4, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by mhoram\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"meyerweb","CreatedById":135212,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-20T17:20:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod has been let go by mhoram\u2014see \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78756-mhoram/\u0026amp;status=2174\u0026amp;type=status\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003Ecom\u003C/abbr\u003E/index.php?/profile/78756-mhoram/\u0026amp;status=2174\u0026amp;type=status\u003C/a\u003E\u2014so if anyone\u2019s interested in picking it up and maintaining it for 1.1\u002B, the field is yours!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-15T09:37:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPublished new version for KSP 1.1.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"meyerweb","CreatedById":135212,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-15T14:13:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222717672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471253854\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278756\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mhoram\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, mhoram said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPublished new version for KSP 1.1.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWOOHOOO!\u00A0 Thanks, mhoram!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Z3R0_0NL1N3","CreatedById":60881,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-16T09:03:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is no dark side of the Mun really. Matter of fact it\u0027s all light.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-16T14:24:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222717840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471270412\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135212\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022meyerweb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 15.8.2016 at 4:13 PM, meyerweb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWOOHOOO!\u00A0 Thanks, mhoram!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are welcome. When I recently installed KSP again, I missed this feature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222718754\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471338207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260881\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Z3R0_0NL1N3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Z3R0_0NL1N3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is no dark side of the Mun really. Matter of fact it\u0027s all light.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, but I am unable to reproduce what you are describing in stock KSP. Perhaps you already have one of the other mentioned similar mods installed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-16T23:29:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222718754\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471338207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260881\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Z3R0_0NL1N3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Z3R0_0NL1N3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is no dark side of the Mun really. Matter of fact it\u0027s all light.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s hardly true... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bombaatu","CreatedById":157643,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-21T15:39:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFYI, the version file is incorrect in 3.2. I downloaded \u0026amp; installed this mod -\u00A0Mini-AVC reports installed version is 3.0.2 instead\u00A03.2 and states there is an upgrade available.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-21T16:29:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222724522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471793951\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157643\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bombaatu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n47 minutes ago, Bombaatu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFYI, the version file is incorrect in 3.2. I downloaded \u0026amp; installed this mod -\u00A0Mini-AVC reports installed version is 3.0.2 instead\u00A03.2 and states there is an upgrade available.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for letting me know. I corrected this and uploaded a new version to spacedock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-25T18:16:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPublished a new version for KSP 1.12.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}